## Content Production: In-House vs Agency

**In-house advantages:**

-   Deep product and industry knowledge
-   Faster turnaround (no briefing overhead)
-   Better cost per piece at scale
-   Integrated with sales feedback

**In-house challenges:**

-   Requires hiring specialist writers
-   Limited bandwidth for consistent production
-   Potential quality inconsistency
-   Difficulty scaling production

**Agency advantages:**

-   Professional writing quality
-   Scalable production capacity
-   Fresh external perspectives
-   Established processes

**Agency challenges:**

-   Requires extensive briefing
-   Higher cost per piece
-   Knowledge transfer overhead
-   Variable quality between agencies

**Hybrid approach works best:**

-   In-house team owns strategy and subject matter expertise
-   Agency/freelancers handle production at scale
-   [Content briefs](/services/content-briefs/) bridge the gap, ensuring external writers produce strategically aligned content

